60|$|The {{other members}} of the household, viz., John and his wife, Leah the housemaid, and Sophie the French nurse, were decent people; but in no respect remarkable; with Sophie I used to talk French, <b>and</b> {{sometimes}} <b>I</b> <b>asked</b> <b>her</b> questions about her native country; but she was not of a descriptive or narrative turn, and generally gave such vapid and confused answers as were calculated rather to check than encourage inquiry.|$|R
